  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AL-02 sensitivity gap)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed across five flow-speed operating points and a verbal screening sensitivity study is noted in the UQ report narrative; however, no structured hasSensitivityAnalysis record is linked to this package, leaving dominant input drivers uncharacterized at the evidence level. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; achieved levels meet or exceed required levels under the accepted decision.",
