      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Input parameters used in validation simulations must be equivalent to those used in the COU predictions. Any differences must be documented and their impact assessed.",
      "rationale": "Validation simulations use identical boundary conditions, fluid properties, and geometric representation as COU predictions. Minor difference in hematocrit (bovine 33% vs human 40%) documented; sensitivity of NIH to hematocrit assessed as less than 3% based on published literature correlations."
