    "rationale": "All 13 credibility factors assessed at or above required levels for MRL 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification confirms NIH predictions remain below the absolute clinical hemolysis threshold across the 95th percentile of the input uncertainty space. Validation uncertainty analysis per ASME V&V 20 demonstrates adequate model accuracy at four of five operating points. The UQ report notes a screening sensitivity study was performed to identify influential inputs, and the assessment team considers the overall evidence package sufficient to support regulatory submission for the Class III VAD indication.",
